<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861211-0020 </DOCNO><HL> CRS Sirrine Acquires49% Stake in DeveloperOf Cogeneration Plants</HL><DD> 12/11/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> DA EFACTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> HOUSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   CRS Sirrine Inc. said it acquired from Energy Factors Inc. and a private investor a 49% interest in a company that is developing wood-fired cogeneration power plants.    Terms and the name of the private investor weren't disclosed. Under the transaction, CRS will provide Midland, Mich.,-based Viking Energy Corp. with engineering, project financing and technical support for its plants. The remaining interest in Viking Energy is retained by Energy Factors.    Viking is currently developing three plants -- in Lincoln and McBain, Mich., and Northumberland, Pa. -- at a total cost of about $70 million. Under long-term agreements, the Michigan plants will sell electricity to Consumer Power Co. and the Northumberland plant will sell power to Pennsylvania Power andamp; Light Co.    CRS is an engineering and architectural services concern. Energy Factors is a San Diego-based energy services company. </TEXT></DOC>